==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Foolishness
<hw>Fool"ish*ness</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The quality of
being foolish.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A foolish practice; an absurdity.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q> The preaching of the cross is to them that perish
<qex>foolishness</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>1 Cor. i. 18.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fool-large</ent>⟦br⟧
